Thing I’ve found with adderall is that it’s very dose dependent for me.

Low dose will give me increased focus which is short lived...

Take more and I become laser focused with a desire to accomplish real work.

Take more and I can’t get any work done because I like the feeling of walking around and /or masturbating too much

More than this and I’m up all night being horny 

More than this and I become psychotic and paranoid where I start hearing voices and thinking people are coming for me.


So, in conclusion, I think adderall is amazing and I’m trying to learn to use it lower doses more productively and fight the urge to redose more often than I should-unless that’s what I’m intentionally going for.

Some of the responses here are on point.  I’d like to offer my own suggestions from my experience.

1.  Tolerance is both physical and psychological / mental.  To reverse total tolerance to the effects of being on adderall you need to discontinue taking it in addition to allowing yourself mental downtime—time spent at your mental baseline.  If you don’t experience the down part of it, the up part loses its distinct qualities.  You become used to the experience of being up and it no longer feels like it’s up.  Time is part of the key here.

2.  As others have stated, you are probably physically low on certain minerals and neurotransmitters.  To recover lost minerals from using stimulants you’ll need a few key supplements.  

Kelp for iodine and micronutrients.  A chelated multi mineral complex for heavy remineralization.  An optimized B-complex to help restore neurotransmitters—Jarrow b-right is a good one, it’s what I use.  Take extra chelated zinc.  Fish oil is also fantastic for neurotransmitters.  Magnesium glycinate is a must—you can also use magnesium glycinate while you are using adderall to help potentiate the effects and alkalize your digestive tract.  

For diet, try eating more grass fed meats and wild fish like Salmon.  Also eat plenty of organic vegetables and whole grains.  Basically a clean and healthy balanced diet.


3. Other things that will really help you:

1. Intense physical exercise or HIIT: exercise spikes neurogenesis which means you create new brain cells and neurons.  You must follow this up with adequate rest and sleep.  

2.  Yoga will quickly reset your body and brain and help you detox while also helping absorb the good nutrients you are taking in from your diet and the supplements

3. Magnesium foot soak - adds magnesium to your body transdermally while also pulling toxins out through your feet.

4.  Dry skin brushing—stimulates lymph system and detoxifies.

5.  Try taking ashwagandha extract and/or Mucuna pruriens extract to help restore neurotransmitters.



Bottom line is that you need some good time not using stimulants while remineralizing your body and brain, and getting plenty of rest and rebuilding your energy stores.

Using adderall or any stimulant is like withdrawing money out of your bioenergetic bank account.  Sooner or later you are going to need to stop withdrawing and start depositing money (energy).

Unfortunately adderall has become harder to get by most psychiatrists, and particularly at the higher dosages which are very effective for many people.

The DEA has put a ton of pressure on doctors as part of the ineffective and failing “war on drugs”.

Definitely do not go on and say you want adderall.  Say that you have a history of poor focus and concentration and are exploring your options for medication that might help.  You may need to “doctor shop” a bit.

Having a note from a therapist also can help and it takes the pressure off of the psychiatrist.
